8 - Master Items and Drill down Functionality 8

Master Items  are dimensions, measures and visualizations that have been saved in the Asset panel in a Qlik Sense app.  During the development process, Master Items can be used to create visualizations and once the app is published, the Master Items are available in the Library panel 

Below are some examples of how to create master items in Qlik Sense 

Name: Conversion rate

Expression: Count(distinct ClassSignupsID) / Count(Distinct [CampaignID-Id])



Name: Campaign Tag(s)

Expression: Count(Distinct MarketingTagName)



Drill downs  are dimensions or measures which can allow  a user to explore different layers of data.  Below is how we create a drill down functionality within our dashboard. This drill down will be saved in master items for later use.  For this drill down, we will use the fields  MarketingTagCategory , MarketingTagName and CampaignName.

                                                                                                                                                


Below are the expressions for the master items. 

Name

Expression

Campaign Tag(s)

Count(Distinct MarketingTagName)

Campaign(s)

Count(Distinct [CampaignID-Id])

Campaign(Test)

Count(MarketingTagName)

Conversion rate

Count(distinct ClassSignupsID) / Count(Distinct [CampaignID-Id])

Conversion(s)

Count(Distinct ClassSignupsID)

Hit Per Campaign %

(Count(PreUserID)/ Sum(WebsiteHits))

Hit Per Campaign % (Test)

(SUM(WebsiteHits)/ Count(DISTINCT CampaignName))

Hit rate

SUM(WebsiteHitsUnique)/COUNT(DISTINCT CampaignName)

Hits

SUM(WebsiteHits)

Lead Conversion

Count(Distinct ClassSignupsID)/COUNT(DISTINCT UserID)

Lead Per Campaign %

Count(Distinct UserID) / Sum (WebsiteHits)

Lead rate

Count(distinct UserID) / Count(Distinct [CampaignID-Id])

Lead(s)

COUNT(DISTINCT UserID)

User(s)

Count(PreUserID)
